                <head>473. Summary of Conclusions of a Special Coordination Committee Meeting<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d473fn1">Source: Washington National Records
                        Center, <gloss target="#t_OSD_1">OSD</gloss> Files, FRC 330–82–0205, Central
                        America Jan.–Aug. 1979. Secret. The meeting took place in the White House
                        Situation Room. <persName corresp="#p_BZ_1">Brzezinski</persName> sent the
                        summary to <persName corresp="#p_VC_1">Vance</persName>, Brown, <persName
                            corresp="#p_MJT_1">McIntyre</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_GJJ_1"
                            >Gilligan</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_JDC_2">Jones</persName>, and
                            <persName corresp="#p_TS_1">Turner</persName> under a July 26
                        memorandum. Brown’s initials appear on this copy of the memorandum. No
                        minutes for this meeting were found.</note>
                </head>
